She said, "To this day, that feeling of inferiority and being different has been what has really given me the power and the strength to succeed".
He wanted to prove that he was "something", he claimed, so he was not disappointed when he finally discovered his sexuality.
The two-time Olympic bronze medalist has become a prominent profile of the LGBT movement and his image has been used at this year's Commonwealth Games held in Australia to call for more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said he told it because he felt lucky to live in freedom, without reprisals, and wanted to pass that "hope" on to other people.
The three-time world champion stated that it was also a surprise for him to fall in love with a man, the American filmmaker Dustin Lance Black, whom he met in 2013.
Daley married last year to the Oscar winner, who has been married to her for 20 years, though she specified that the age difference had never been an issue.
"When you live so long from so young" (he went to his first Olympics at 14 and his father died of cancer three years later), it's hard to find someone your age who has been through the same ups and downs as you.
