American star Phil Mickelson, who had to fight through most of the tournament, threw his starting point into the water on the 16th hole, par 3, thus admitting defeat to Francesco Molinari.
Italian golfer Molinari excelled in all of his rounds, becoming one of only four players to ever achieve a 5-0-0 record since the tournament's current format began in 1979.
The American Jordan Spieth was defeated 5-4 by the lowest ranked player in the European team, the Dane Thorbjorn Olesen.
The world's number one player, Dustin Johnson, fell 2 and 1 to Englishman Ian Poulter, who could have played his last Ryder Cup.
Spaniard Sergio Garcia, a veteran who has won eight Ryder Cups, became the European player with the most tournament wins of all time, with 25.5 career points.
I don't usually cry, but today I can't help it.
It's been a very tough year.
I'm totally grateful to Thomas for choosing me and believing in me.
I'm very, very happy that I was able to get the cup back.
It is an achievement of the whole team and I am very happy to have been able to help", said an excited Garcia after the victory of the European team.
He now passes the torch to his compatriot John Rahm, who already beat American golf legend Tiger Woods 2-1 in a singles match on Sunday.
"I feel incredibly proud to have beaten Tiger Woods, as I grew up watching this man", said 23-year-old golfer John Rahm.
Woods lost all four matches in France and now has a 13-21-3 record in his Ryder Cup career.
That's a strange statistic for one of the greatest players of all time, who has won 14 major titles, second only to Jack Nicklaus.
The American team had to struggle all weekend to find the streets, with the exception of Patrick Reed, Justin Thomas and Tony Finau, who played top-level golf throughout the tournament.
American captain Jim Furyk spoke after his team's disappointing performance: "I'm very proud of these guys, they never stopped fighting.
There was a moment this morning when we heated up the situation in Europe.
But we blew it.
I want to congratulate Thomas.
He's a great captain.
Your 12 players have played a very good game.
We regroup, I'll meet with the PGA of America and our Ryder Cup Committee, and we'll move on.
I love these 12 boys very much and I'm proud to be their captain.
Now we have to bow our heads.
They've outrun us.
Red tide update: Concentrations are decreasing in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota.
The new report from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows an overall reduction in red tide concentrations in areas of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, irregular flowering conditions are being reported in areas of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier counties, suggesting a reduction in concentrations.
The red tide bloom extends approximately along 130 miles of coastline from Pinellas County in the north to Lee County in the south.
Irregular plots can be found about 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough County, but in fewer places compared to last week.
Red tide has also been detected in Pasco County.
Over the past week, medium concentrations have been reported in Pinellas County and its coastline, low to high concentrations in Hillsborough County coastline, low to high concentrations in Manatee County, low to high concentrations in Sarasota County and its coastline, low to medium concentrations in Charlotte County, low to high concentrations in Lee County and its coastline, and low concentrations in Collier County.
Respiratory irritation problems are still being reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier counties.
There have been no reports of respiratory irritation problems in the northwest Florida area during the past week.
